@node Recompiling the source code,,Troubleshooting compile errors,Compile the source code
@anchor{install recompiling-the-source-code}@anchor{1c}
@subsubsection Recompiling the source code


If you plan to use @code{make confsource} to recompile your source, you should
first issue a @code{make clean} before re-issuing a @code{make confsource}

A failure to issue @code{make clean} prior to re-compiling with @code{make confsource}
can potentially leave stale object files which may cause unforseen issues when
running code, including but not limited to random crashes.  Generally whenever
recompiling it's good to always make clean first.

@cartouche
@quotation Note 
You may also issue @code{make source} if the @code{Makefile} is already defined how
you want it to be.  Please remember to @code{make clean} before @code{make source`}
whenever you alter the code or import new source code.
